article.headline: UC Davis 62, Pacific 59
article.story: DAVIS, Calif. -- Julian Welch had 19 points in a reserve role to help UC Davis beat Pacific 62-59 and stop a 49-game losing streak to the Tigers that dated back to the 1940-41 season. Dominic Calegari had 13 points, seven rebounds, and three key free throws for the Aggies (10-13, 6-5 Big Sky). Terrell Smith had 16 points and Michael Nunnally scored 13 points for the Tigers (15-8, 8-3). The Tigers fell into a first-place tie with UC Santa Barbara. Calegari made three straight free throws to make the score 60-58 with 1:08 seconds remaining. Joe Harden added another free throw with 34-seconds remaining, it was his two shots from the charity stripe with 12-seconds to play that sealed the victory for the Aggies. The Aggies were without their leading scorer and point guard Mark Payne, who was out with an illness.
